on and its effect on humans and the environment, and the technological and individual measures needed to address these challenges. The book also functions as a handbook for more environmentally conscious living by providing information on alternative energy sources for consumers and tips for cleaner running cars. * Features 80 color photographs, 23 figures, 18 maps* Covers regional differences of topography, weather, and the character of the air in California’s fifteen designated air basins* Includes a field guide to the sky, explaining color and light, clouds and wind, and the nature of flight* Addresses issues surrounding global climate change in CaliforniaA book in the Californians and Their Environment subseries, dedicated to understanding human influences on the state's ecology and natural resources  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAir qualityzCalifornia. 0aAirxPollutionzCalifornia. 0aAtmosphere. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Meteorology & Climatology.2bisacsh  aair basins.  aair feel.  aair pollution.  aair quality management.  aair quality.  aair smell.  aair taste.  aalternative energy sources.  aatmospheric gases.  abreathable air.  acalifornia history.  acalifornia.  acentral valley.  acleaner cars.  aclimate change.  acolor photographs.  aconsumer society.  aenvironmental impact.  ahuman impact.  anatural history guide.  anatural history.  anatural resources.  anonfiction.  aseasonal climate.  asky phenomena.  asustainability.  atopography.  aweather patterns.  awind patterns.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024531040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093955440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939554423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.c